The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 February is 39,685 (4,593.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 February, there were 760 new confirmed cases (88.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 February, there were 1,057 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (297 fewer cases).
